<subSubSection id="3D572410BDFC276FF45A8B5317E841C1" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D7E6E07499A7AA7ABDA4AA211CCE2903" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D200C1D7FCF571CDE6AD2A0E754302F3" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="574776F79A1F8D514053D76B74651E56" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">speciosus</emphasis>
(Latin), beautiful, showy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AA1EBC3A1778D576B12936E18F9BDDE6" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" type="nomenclatural comments">
<paragraph id="C43F5CDD98594BCEEE49EDCE2DD9D057" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Nomenclatural comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3AC1BF8C2606835D8846D755196C212F" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
The binomials 
<taxonomicName id="E1FE8D9F83AB16B2BDCB9FF7E8A815BD" authorityName="Nees" authorityYear="1841" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Gynerium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gynerium speciosum" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="speciosum">
<emphasis id="40FED9E26E45801F2CCF90616440F198" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Gynerium speciosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="1545565D31BCD705523EA57A0601016F" authorityName="Meyen" authorityYear="1834" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Gynerium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gynerium neesii" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="neesii">
<emphasis id="8A0F81661C90DF557ED220E847415330" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Gynerium neesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0979810D41F903DD7F88CBF5AEA89DEE" authorityName="Meyen" authorityYear="1834" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Gynerium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gynerium pygmaeum" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pygmaeum">
<emphasis id="A5407C2FD547BDBE3F111B52E617DF06" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Gynerium pygmaeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- mentioned as new species by Meyen (1834), from Copiapo (Chile) and Lake Titicaca (Peru), respectively - are synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="234BCCCC4E14DC4FA6CA1C451810C4AF" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cortaderia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cortaderia speciosa" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis id="19EBC1329E30D2CC7700B0E24DF01F22" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Cortaderia speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but are invalid (nomina nuda) as no descriptions were published. Their identity can be determined, because the specimens in B! were annotated with the Meyen names. 
<taxonomicName id="518CC2443A6B5630E1559F3B497E8868" authorityName="Nees" authorityYear="1841" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Gynerium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gynerium speciosum" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="speciosum">
<emphasis id="0AB175768592FE7530A24A2DF19E3320" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Gynerium speciosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was validated by Nees in 1943. Tropicos (Downloaded 14 December 2016) lists the species as described by Nees in 1841 (
<bibRefCitation id="FD32DEE27E34C20AC75E9C8E03B8BCAF" author="Nees ab Esenbeck, CG" journalOrPublisher="Prausnitzianis, Glogau" pageId="27" pageNumber="66" refId="B25" refString="Nees ab Esenbeck, CG, 1841. Florae Africae Australioris. Illustrationis monographicae. I. Gramineae. Prausnitzianis, Glogau" title="Florae Africae Australioris. Illustrationis monographicae. I. Gramineae" year="1841">Nees ab Esenbeck 1841</bibRefCitation>
), but this is erroneous. 
<bibRefCitation id="591875B8D0441833D9B7F64FD86F76C7" author="Conert, J" journalOrPublisher="Cramer, Weinheim" pageId="26" pageNumber="65" refId="B5" refString="Conert, J, 1961. Die Systematik und Anatomie der Arundineae. J. Cramer, Weinheim" title="Die Systematik und Anatomie der Arundineae. J." year="1961">Conert (1961)</bibRefCitation>
designated 
<emphasis id="33C993B1212C5069E6F2B956688755B9" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Philippi 1024</emphasis>
(B photo!) from Chile (&quot;Atacama oppidum, 1824&quot;) as lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="62B8840164632E1509D3BC8589BC910D" authorityName="Phil" authorityYear="1864" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Gynerium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gynerium atacamense" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="atacamense">
<emphasis id="6A4B1EA0651F116D0516AD032A915D3F" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Gynerium atacamense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Phil. However, the type has been found in the herbarium SGO (Connor, 1983) and, therefore, the lectotype designated by Conert should not be taken into account. The binomial 
<taxonomicName id="61ECF8D3ABF3C52EACA2AD2CA82FAF79" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Arundo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Arundo quila" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="quila">
<emphasis id="A506583B997FC3C2B73AC2FB9605CFC1" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Arundo quila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Molina is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="6188D891373FD3D98E49EC98A7C2FCB6" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Chusquea quila" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="species" species="quila">
<emphasis id="90E6F6E1E99F01F9C4BCB58E71B14E4B" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Chusquea quila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kunth (
<taxonomicName id="8180CE260FB4658134684858C03C23B6" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1822" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" phylum="Liliopsida" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Bambusoideae">Bambusoideae</taxonomicName>
). In some works, it has been confused 
<taxonomicName id="51B8509B24131A321F35AF2986DBC530" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Gynerium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gynerium quila" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="quila">
<emphasis id="0AA610827EE4BF03E4740094439540DB" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Gynerium quila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nees &amp; Meyen (basionym of 
<taxonomicName id="9192346FF754FC2EF07BDA7EB3ED924E" authorityName="Stapf" authorityYear="1897" baseAuthorityName="Molina" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cortaderia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cortaderia quila" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="quila">
<emphasis id="9FF8B44697A1951C6506D5022A55D067" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Cortaderia quila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nees &amp; Meyen) Stapf, therefore, the binomials 
<taxonomicName id="C0C3F401E597A369E5D669D42039C12D" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Gynerium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gynerium quila" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="quila">
<emphasis id="95FB5B3C85422926A6F076E99D4509B5" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Gynerium quila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Molina) Nees &amp; Meyen and 
<taxonomicName id="CC7CB3C955A5E042402B2CEC3A051864" authorityName="Stapf" authorityYear="1897" baseAuthorityName="Molina" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cortaderia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cortaderia quila" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="quila">
<emphasis id="AE7367E526B236A81F74EAD1E40D2B96" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Cortaderia quila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Molina) Stapf are invalid.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="84BFACAC55D7EED381A6A7313B9831A0" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" type="common names">
<paragraph id="6EB159B3D03DD38E2F19352A32DC4489" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Common names.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FAFE2E7C96DCBF853BAE6441EDF9A5B1" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">cortadera</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3DEA792C9898B9B3349DCBDDBBE1B46E" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" type="taxonomy">
<paragraph id="C2D062EC12D5AF9E107AB21F337AA2EF" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Taxonomy.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F4B9B679191AEF7934F3E86E72F0427" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
In the Selloana group, 
<taxonomicName id="963EBCEB6272E391AF3D1DA3C883EC7E" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cortaderia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cortaderia speciosa" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis id="4AF44486DF71C377438583BED28280A6" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Cortaderia speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be diagnosed by the short basal lemmas, which are less than 13 mm long. The spikelets are 8-15 mm long and the basal lemma 7.0-12.5 mm long (including awn, 1-4 mm). It differs from other species in the group by its very compact, bright brown panicles with ascending, short and stiff 
<pageBreakToken id="34F2DE7E828DD3A3BF5349F37884E25F" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" start="start">branches</pageBreakToken>
. The species is readily distinguished by the small floret sizes. The leaf anatomy is also somewhat different from the other species of the group (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F4976271B1034E4B738DEE62F3B89291" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Leaf anatomy of Cortaderia, as evident from transverse sections. A-B Cortaderia selloana (Villamil 11738) C Cortaderia speciosa (Testoni 644) D Cortaderia vaginata (Zanin 1654). Comparison of bulliform cells in Egmontiana group: E Cortaderia egmontiana (Testoni 634) F Cortaderia modesta (Carauta 927) G Cortaderia vaginata (Zanin 1654). Structures referred to in the descriptions are labelled as follows: 1, multi-layered abaxial sub-epidermal collenchyma layer; 2, aerenchyma; 3, chlorenchyma; 4, primary vascular bundle; 5, midrib; 6, colourless cells; 7, empty cells; 8, bulliform cells." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.76.10808.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/117856" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">2C</figureCitation>
): the midrib is rounded and somewhat lower; the outer sheath of the central vascular bundle without projections to the adaxial epidermis; and with a massive abaxial sub-epidermal collenchyma layer, only in the middle part of the leaf. The latter occurs in the Nitida group but along the leaf. It is known only by pistillate plants from desert regions (the Puna) of Argentina, Bolivia and Chile.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CB8E713EF8A4806612B0970AFF2038A7" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">
This species is completely apomictic, and several morphological subgroups can be recognized. As these are all apomicts, it is presumed that they derive from the same ancestral sexual population. The material previously separated as 
<taxonomicName id="4E8720370F3BEFD0695CEB1659D344FA" authorityName="Stapf" authorityYear="1897" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cortaderia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cortaderia rudiuscula" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rudiuscula">
<emphasis id="DF52283AA290AE0AB87AB9B58767BCC4" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Cortaderia rudiuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has longer (9-12 mm) and more slender lemmas, than the material previously separated as 
<taxonomicName id="99047B7C490C22C22CEA9F2D8E9C5502" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cortaderia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cortaderia speciosa" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis id="BD2063F0C77D325372F2FE7C45695E83" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Cortaderia speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(lemmas ca. 8 mm), but there is no clear separation between these two forms.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
